      "content": "recharge... i don't think i can just \"recharge.\" it feels more like the battery is completely gone, like it's never coming back. every time i try to think about the future, it's just this massive, heavy wall of nothingness. even if i sleep for a week, the reality is still there. the failure is still there. i just feel like i've reached the end of the road and there's nowhere left to go. it feels like the only way to actually get that quiet i'm talking about is to just... stop everything for good.",
